  "texts": [
    "Extreme values in time series, representing rare but impactful events like surge in electricity demand or natural disasters, pose unique challenges to forecasting accuracy.",
    "These extreme values can significantly skew predictions if not properly accounted for, highlighting the need for robust models and techniques that specifically address the complexities of handling extreme values in forecasting.",
    "In simple terms, extreme values are those that are much larger or smaller than the typical range of the time series.",
    "The data distribution of such extreme values remains different compared to those of normally distributed data in time series like heavy rainfall and floods, abrupt changes in stock indices, or substantial traffic surges.",
    "In this paper, we present a customizable framework for time series forecasting that emphasizes modeling both extreme and normal values to minimize overall prediction error."
  ],
